Docker Deploy Steps:

1. Start private registry on port 5000.
2. Start init-script.sh to do the following tasks:
	- Build a new docker image for a simple node.js app. 
	- Push the new docker image to the registry.
	- Deploy the App to Blue slice on port 50100 and Green slice on port 50101. 
3. Check if the app is running in both the containers. 
4. Change the message in the main.js file. 
5. A commit will build a new docker image and push to the local registery. 
6. Deploy the dockerized simple node.js App to blue slice. 
7. Check the updated message. 
8. Deploy the dockerized simple node.js App to green slice.
9. Check the updated message. 
